{"word":"παλαιστής","slug":"παλαιστής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παλαιστής</b></el> <el>(πᾰλαιστής, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:παλαίω'><el>παλαίω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a wrestler</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>a rival, adversary</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: <i>a candidate, suitor</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}